VarAttributes.CATDESC: Default time

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: MMS2 FPI/DIS burst data begin-time; derived from burst packet time.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS epoch plus var

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: MMS2 FPI/DIS epoch plus var

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS epoch minus var

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: MMS2 FPI/DIS epoch minus var

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS 32-bit vector of data-quality indicators at burst-start time

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Value of zero signifies no quality errors. For non-zero values: Bit-0 = manually flagged interval, Bit-1 = overcounting/saturation effects likely present in skymap, Bit-2 = reported spacecraft potential above 20V, Bit-3 = invalid/unavailable spacecraft potential, Bit-4 = significant (>25%) cold plasma (<10eV) component, Bit-5 = significant (>25%) hot plasma (>30keV) component, Bit-6 = high sonic Mach number (v/vth > 2.5), Bit-7 = low calculated density (n_DIS < 0.05 cm^-3), Bit-8 = bentPipe magnetic field used instead of brst l2pre magnetic field, Bit-9 = srvy l2pre magnetic field used instead of brst l2pre magnetic field, Bit-10 = no internally generated photoelectron correction applied

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS2 FPI/DIS compression lossless/lossy indicator at survey-start time

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: FPI/DIS compression loss indicator, 0=lossless, 1=lossy

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS2 FPI/DIS step table parity, this burst

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: FPI/DIS alternates between two tables, designated "even" (0) and "odd" (1).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS2 FPI/DIS Del-Phi (obs spin-phase) count at burst-start time

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Nominally, spin-phase counts range over [0000, 5759] cnts.  Each count represents 1/16 deg of observatory spin-phase.  Zero spin-phase count indicates obs +X-axis aligned with Sun.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS2 FPI/DIS Del-Phi (obs spin-phase) angle at burst-start time

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Nominally, spin-phase angles range over [0, 360) deg.  Each count represents 1/16 deg of observatory spin-phase.  Zero spin-phase angle indicates obs +X-axis aligned with Sun.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS2 FPI/DIS sector de-Spin P value, this burst

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Records P-value used to de-spin this burst sky-map on board.  See FPI docs for details.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS ion energy spectrum "near" +X_DSC during this burst

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Counts, summed over DSC velocity-dirs closest to +X_DSC, by energy bin.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Counts, summed over DSC velocity-dirs closest to -X_DSC, by energy bin.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS omni-directional ion energy spectrum during this burst

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Differential energy flux, averaged (weighted by solid angle) over all look directions, by energy bin.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS ion background energy during this burst

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Background differential energy flux by energy bin, averaged (weighted by solid angle) over all directions (flow or look) background level.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS2 FPI/DIS ion background number density during this burst

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Background number density derived via integration of the estimated background differential energy flux.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS FPI/DIS pitch-bin index used in some types of outputs

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: pitch-angle bins: pitch index=00 bins quasi-parallel to B, ..., pitch index=29 bins quasi-anti-parallel to B.  pitch-angle bin size: 6 deg.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS/FPI energy-bin index used in some types of outputs

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: FPI operations nominally bin data from 64 energy filters into 32 pairwise energy bins, indexed 0-31.  Nominally, bins are indexed in increasing energy order.  See FPI docs for details.
